rComments: Course content is excellent, but Ong's lectures wander because she doesn't seem to put much effort into them. Agreed w/ the previous reviewer that she seems like she's just winging it. Course is good b/c there are a bunch of films and she rarely tests on the content of the readings. Her TA marks easy and is flexible on extensions though!

Are we listening to the same professor? Her lectures are horrible and she gives the impression that she cares more about her own research and whatever else than she does about teaching. I don't know how many times she repeated herself in her lectures. It's as if she were a high school student winging their presentation and hoping no one notices
Amazing seminar classes with Prof Ong. She's sharp and insightful, and encourages class participation. Prepare to work hard and you'll learn a great deal.
Great prof, clear lectures. She has a solid drip on China's political system, and she understands the nuances. People say she is a tough marker, but if you work hard, you can get an A.

I took Prof. Ong's China in the World  seminar. It's a first year seminar course with twenty or so students. She's harder than the average not because she's evil but because she teaches masters level courses. It's a benefit because the content of the course surpasses the average first year level and you can get a lot out of it if you WORK.
She knows her stuff really well and is able to explain difficult subject matter lucidly. I recommend her class to anyone who is serious about learning.

Prof Ong is a great professor. She is patient with her students and is willing to go the extra miles that most other profs I know won't. She maybe a tough grader but she makes sure that those who got an "A" really deserves one.

Her lectures can be a bit dry sometimes.  But I still do think she's a great prof.  I found her fairly helpful and accessible, relatively generous with grading, and above all she really knows her stuff well. You just gotta love her jokes and her gifted ability of making boring materials really interesting.  I'd recommend her class to anyone.
She's an awesome prof! I recommend taking her classes.
incompetent in her teaching abilities. must work on her lectures and exams
